{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Capitalize Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Capitalize Filter</h1>

<p>Converts the first character of a string to uppercase. The remaining characters are left unchanged.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "string" | capitalize %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "hello world" | capitalize %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Hello world</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "already Capitalized" | capitalize %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Already Capitalized</p>
<p>If the first character is already uppercase, the string is returned unchanged.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "ALL CAPS INPUT" | capitalize %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> ALL CAPS INPUT</p>
<p>Only the first character is affected — the rest of the string is not lowercased. To ensure a fully normalized result, chain with <code>downcase</code> first: <code>| downcase | capitalize</code>.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Only the first byte is uppercased; the remaining characters are untouched.</li>
  <li>Unlike some implementations, <code>capitalize</code> does <strong>not</strong> lowercase the rest of the string.</li>
  <li>To capitalize with the rest lowercased, use <code>| downcase | capitalize</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/upcase">upcase</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/downcase">downcase</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
